---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="ban.gs — query type benchmark"
  description="Measure redirect latency across query types and verify that the local-first route stays fast under repeated runs."
  currentPath="/bench"
  pageScript="bench"
>
  <div
    id="sw-status"
    class="warning hidden rounded-[20px] px-4 py-3 text-sm mb-4"
  ></div>

  <div class="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,0.7fr)_minmax(0,1fr)]">
    <aside class="card h-fit p-5 sm:p-6">
      <p class="text-xs font-700 uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-primary-700">
        What this checks
      </p>
      <h1
        class="mt-2 font-display text-[2.4rem] font-800 leading-tight tracking-[-0.04em] text-text sm:text-[2.8rem]"
      >
        Benchmark
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-text-secondary">
        The benchmark stops at the Service Worker redirect response. That
        isolates routing overhead from the destination site’s network latency.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-4 grid gap-3">
        <div class="rounded-[20px] bg-bg-soft p-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-700 text-text">Warmup included</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-text-secondary">
            Each query type gets a warmup phase first to stabilize caches.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-[20px] bg-bg-soft p-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-700 text-text">High-resolution clock</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-text-secondary">
            Results use <code>performance.now()</code> for per-iteration
            timings.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-[20px] bg-bg-soft p-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-700 text-text">Compare spread</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-text-secondary">
            Median, mean, p95, p99, min, and max make regressions easier to
            spot.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </aside>

    <div class="grid gap-4">
      <div class="card">
        <h2 class="section-title mb-3">Configuration</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
          <label for="iterations" class="label-text">
            Iterations per query type
          </label>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 sm:flex-row">
            <input
              type="text"
              id="iterations"
              value="500"
              inputmode="numeric"
              class="input-field w-full sm:!w-48"
            />
            <button
              type="button"
              class="btn-primary whitespace-nowrap"
              id="run-btn"
            >
              Run Benchmark
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div id="progress" class="hidden">
          <div class="mt-4 h-[5px] overflow-hidden rounded-full bg-bg-strong">
            <div class="progress-fill" id="progress-fill"></div>
          </div>
          <div
            class="mt-2 text-[0.82rem] text-text-secondary"
            id="progress-text"
          ></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hidden" id="results-section">
        <div class="card mb-4">
          <h2 class="section-title">Detailed Statistics</h2>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="stats-table mt-4 text-[0.8rem]" id="stats-table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Query Type</th>
                  <th>Median</th>
                  <th>Mean</th>
                  <th>p95</th>
                  <th>p99</th>
                  <th>Min</th>
                  <th>Max</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody id="stats-body"></tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card mb-4 hidden" id="summary-card">
          <div class="py-3 text-center text-[0.98rem] font-700" id="summary"></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2 class="section-title mb-3">Methodology</h2>
        <div class="text-[0.9rem] leading-[1.8] text-text-secondary">
          <p class="mb-3">
            Each query type is benchmarked independently using
            <code class="font-mono text-[0.85em]">
              fetch('/?q=...', &#123; redirect: 'manual' &#125;)
            </code>
            which stops at the Service Worker’s 302 redirect response without
            following it. This measures the actual SW processing time with no
            network overhead.
          </p>
          <ul class="my-2 ml-5">
            <li class="mb-1">
              <strong>50 warmup iterations</strong>
              per query type (discarded) to stabilize caches
            </li>
            <li class="mb-1">
              <strong>500 measured iterations</strong>
              by default (configurable 100–5,000)
            </li>
            <li class="mb-1">
              <strong>performance.now()</strong>
              for high-resolution timing per iteration
            </li>
            <li class="mb-1">
              Stats computed: <strong>median</strong>, mean, p95, p99, min, max
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Run with DevTools <strong>closed</strong> because Chrome adds heavy
            instrumentation overhead to Service Worker timing.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style is:inline>
    .warning {
      color: #9a6700;
      background: rgba(255, 244, 214, 0.9);
      border: 1px solid rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.28);
      box-shadow: 0 12px 28px rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.08);
    }
    .warning a {
      color: #9a6700;
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
    .progress-fill {
      width: 0%;
      height: 100%;
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, #60a5fa, #0f766e);
      transition: width 0.1s;
    }
    .stats-table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
    }
    .stats-table th {
      padding: 0.65rem 0.7rem;
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #58708c;
      text-align: left;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #d7e3ef;
    }
    .stats-table td {
      padding: 0.6rem 0.7rem;
      font-family:
        ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #e6eef8;
    }
    .stats-table tr td:first-child {
      font-family: inherit;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: #16324f;
    }
    .stats-table .fastest {
      color: #1d8f6d;
    }
    .summary-value {
      font-family:
        ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
      color: #1d8f6d;
    }
    :root[data-theme="dark"] .warning {
      color: #facc15;
      background: rgba(71, 47, 8, 0.76);
      border-color: rgba(250, 204, 21, 0.2);
      box-shadow: 0 12px 28px rgba(2, 6, 23, 0.28);
    }
    :root[data-theme="dark"] .warning a {
      color: #fcd34d;
    }
    :root[data-theme="dark"] .stats-table th {
      color: #8fa7c1;
      border-bottom-color: rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.16);
    }
    :root[data-theme="dark"] .stats-table td {
      border-bottom-color: rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.12);
      color: #d9e6f5;
    }
    :root[data-theme="dark"] .stats-table tr td:first-child {
      color: #eff6ff;
    }
    :root[data-theme="dark"] .stats-table .fastest,
    :root[data-theme="dark"] .summary-value {
      color: #34d399;
    }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
